         hehe how about this... back when it was a ultra-rare drop ONLY off Innoruuk... pre-Velious...</P><P>I was in Dreadlands, just killed the Widow for my Drachnid Thyxl, I get a tell from a guild buddy of mine.. something like "GET TO HATE NOW!"</P><P>Within a few minutes, I get a Wizzy friend to port me up, and a Mage CoH's me to Inny's corpse.  I looted the book.</P><P>At first, I had no idea what it was, really, haha I remember being upset because it didn't have stats on it (&lt;-- n00b).  There wasn't much talk about the book back then becuase it was so damn rare.  I remember posting about it, and someone said it was a fraud, and that I was lying about getting it, hehe.</P><P>Also, as mentioned, it summons your pet at another level higher than it would have summoned, but not always the max level.  That equates basically to a pet that hits +2 harder than if summoned without the book.  Some Necros insist that they also have more HPs, but I dont know about that.  One thing I can tell you, they are bigger than a normal pet, even the specs.</P><P>At 60, I uncommonly summon a 71 hitter (book max) Spec.</P><P>As far as I know, it still only drops in Hate, with the demi's people have already mentioned.</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a></P><P>Edited by - Xuraz on 06/17/2002  08:42:19<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
